             <p align="justify">“Diwali” – a festival in which people of different age groups celebrate and enjoy the festival uniquely but together with their family & friends. Everyone is eagerly waiting and excited too, for the festival of lights. But there are some families who cannot enjoy and celebrate this festival as everyone else does, due to some circumstances. The student of Prayas also belongs to these families and volunteers of Prayas tries there best to fulfilthere wishes.</p>
              <p align="justify">Prayas volunteers organises a Diwali celebration event every year for their children. Here, the children of Prayas are being surprised with the different gifts like clothes, sweets, food, footwears, etc.Prayas children are also being acknowledged to celebrate the Diwali without fire crackers because of there adverse effect on our environment</p>
              
             
