              <p align="justify">Picnic is the most joyful and adventurous part of schooling. Every student in their schooling period wishes to go on a picnic with their friends. Many of them can often go to the picnics organized by their schools but not all children are such fortunate to enjoy and experience those joyful moments with their friends. Students of Prayas belongs to the deprived society and they might not able to go to such picnics. </p>
              <p align="justify">Every year Prayas organizes a picnic for these children. The picnic is arranged at places where the children can enjoy their trip and also learn something beside books.</p>
            <p align="justify">Kids are taken to places like Akshardham where they can learn about peace, harmony and Indian history; Adalaj stepwell so that they can know our ancient talent of carving; Gandhi Ashram so that they can understand thi lifestyle of Mahatma Gandhi,etc.</p>  
              
